-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Java Encapsulation :-

    1) Encapsulation refers to the bundling of fields and methods inside a single class.
    2) It prevents outer classes from accessing and changing fields and methods of a class, This also helps to achieve data hiding.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Data Hiding :-

    1) Data Hiding is a way of restricting the access of our data members by hiding the implementation details.
    2) Encapsulation also provides a way for data hiding.
    3) We can use access modifiers to achieve data hiding.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Note :-   1) People often consider encapsulation as data hiding, but that's not entirely true.
          2) Encapsulation refers to the bundling of related fields and methods together. This can be used to achieve data hiding.
          3) Encapsulation in itself is not data hiding.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------